 Indian colts bag title

 - 4-nation hockey Draw with Chile proves enough 

New Delhi: In a morale-booster ahead of the junior World Cup, the Indian colts won the four-nation hockey tournament in Bilbao, Spain after drawing their last match with Chile 2-2 Monday. 

The competition, featuring strong teams like Holland and Spain, saw India finishing undefeated with two wins and a draw to end with five points, one more than runners-up Holland, according to information received here. 

The World Cup holders had beaten the Dutch in their opening encounter before downing Spain. 

Mondays draw versus Chile, who finished at the bottom of the table, ensured that they go to the World Cup, starting later this month in Rotterdam, with a positive mindset. 

In another match of the day, Holland beat Spain to finish second with two wins ? their other victory coming vs Chile. 

Drag-flicker Sandeep Singh was declared the Player of the Tournament while Adrian DSouza was named the Best Goalkeeper. 

The Indian team will now proceed to Frankfurt, for a seven-day training-cum-practice matches session before moving to Rotterdam for the mega event. (PTI) 




